Don't you need three \ characters to get Lucene to escape it.  With only
one \ you are just escaping the " so that Java doesn't see it as closing
the string literal:

String s =3D "9\" Speaker";     // 9" Speaker  - Lucene thinks it starts =
a
phrase
String s =3D "9\\\" Speaker";   // 9\" Speaker - The " is escaped when
passed to Lucene

Darran

