Hello,
I am new to Lucene, and during my development, I observed that...

the articles indexed last were the articles that were returned first, in =
the results. As if the index was a LIFO. Now this is perfectly =
acceptable as long as we need to get the latest documents. (articles on =
WSJ published today were indexed today, nad hence are more recent and =
more relevant). But I also have to index the older articles.  So, I have =
2 questions...
1. Is my observation correct?
2. I was wondering if anybody had similar problems, and how did they fix =
it?


thanks
Samir

