Ok.. currently Autonomy is used as an extensive search engine on our site.
Until now we used to return results after searching through several external
sites using the spider/categorizer components of autonomy. And now our
own site has grown enof that we have all the info necessary in our web site
itself. So we do not need autonomy for such an internal search (and the
costs
involved). All we need is a search engine which will search through our
website and return those specific pages as links which is of interest to the

user.

i hope that is clear..
-anoop

